"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/Loss of the IL4 cytokine is highly unlikely on tumour tissue as it would be self-effacing for the tumour to no longer express it..md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/Loss of the IL4 cytokine is highly unlikely on tumour tissue as it would be self-effacing for the tumour to no longer express it..md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/Loss of the IL4 cytokine is highly unlikely on tumour tissue as it would be self-effacing for the tumour to no longer express it..md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Loss of the IL4 cytokine is highly unlikely on tumour tissue as it would be self-effacing for the tumour to no longer express it..md#Loss of the IL4 cytokine is highly unlikely on tumour tissue as it would be self-effacing for the tumour to no longer express it. This cytokine is promotes tumour growth by inhibiting tumour-directed Th1-polarized effector T-cell responses.  Downstream, this downregulates proinflammatory signal and upregulates anti-inflammatory (Th2-polarizing) cytokines.{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Loss of the IL4 cytokine is highly unlikely on tumour tissue as it would be self-effacing for the tumour to no longer express it..md#References":true},"mtime":1687939500522,"size":496,"hash":"831b3cfe1d01f27ef959cad251b7ec12434f00695da0cfd4fe4a5847a1757dde"}],"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.00821662,-0.00618392,-0.02284918,0.03588308,0.04961152,-0.0013464,0.03032213,-0.03480463,-0.00629533,-0.00159975,-0.0142363,-0.01777986,-0.02888403,-0.04846552,0.02773353,-0.00190956,0.02885608,-0.00491042,0.00665935,-0.0160104,0.04777712,-0.01494711,-0.00378494,0.02784184,-0.03972679,-0.01871343,0.00818096,0.00398697,-0.05888642,-0.06330485,-0.00567871,0.00355803,0.04589085,0.01691423,0.01350313,-0.00076704,0.00908788,-0.01425117,0.01034552,-0.0328971,-0.02932425,-0.00023189,0.00514885,0.00377877,0.02041023,0.04893675,0.02993241,0.00900545,-0.00009123,0.03520092,-0.02696356,-0.01149579,0.00096093,0.01838762,-0.03